title: GTA 5 - Review
author: @Iser1999
comment: I find it hilarious that people compare gta5 to cyberpunk. Yeah i get it the game is buggy, physics are better in gta5, but they are 100% diferrent games. Gta is not an rpg. Gta5 was fun even though the story was a little bit dull, and the game does have little content outside the story compared to san andreas for example. Overall a fun game but you can easily see that rockstar used most of their forces to make it the best online game, and not the best in storymode. On the other hand, cyberpunk is all about story and it's rpg mechanics and choice making... Buggy... Yeah... Unfinished... Yeah.... Bad?.. Hell no. A much more comparable title would be the cult classic vampire the masquerade bloodlines. Unusually similar.. Very intriguing story and amazing choice making and character customization in an immersive world that feels real, but both are buggy as hell

And pointless missions, such Trevor stealing that war head, making the gamer go through all that effort for nothing, is just plain f*cking stupid. Vice City is still the most popular GTA because of all¬†the sh*t you can do, and the story line. The same can be said about San Andreas. GTA V didn't even utilize any of the many gangs on the game. It just wasn't worth a 5 year wait.

title: GTA 5 - Review
author: @KenTurney
comment:
Feel like this game was a bit over hyped.. don't get me wrong I just finished playing the story for the 5th time.. it's an amazing game.. one of the best games I've ever played.. however I noticed a lot of things that could be improved.
1. The story could have better writing in some areas.. some big moments in the game are ruined by cliche writing.
2. The endings were all pretty weak imo and if you don't choose C loose ends aren't explained.
3. The cover system could take notes from games like the division
4. Mission diversity was much better than previous GTA games but could be better
5. Upgrading weapons could be better maybe take a level system from like an RPG game or something.. adding most attachments don't make a difference
6. Cool things like buying houses and stuff can't be done in story but can be done in online
7. Adding a female lead would be dope
8. Make pricing for things more realistic
9. Make the world interactive.. go in more buildings break walls
10. Some of the heist and other missions should have been longer and maybe more exciting some of them seemed to be a let down
11. Take away some of the dumb cliche stuff and stop trying to make it so funny.. some of the jokes they make or the news that comes on or things that are reality in this game are just foolish
12. Make the missions realistic so you're not just like god murdering everybody and unstoppable
13. Make the missions real so that you have to do things to keep from getting caught instead of just doing whatever and never having a chance of the cops catching you after flying a huge chopper through the sky with a train hanging from it

title: GTA 5 - Review
author: @angelcortez8158
comment: Even though this is a great game I would really like it if rockstar added a few more things in the future. I would actually like to be able to live a normal life meaning getting a job, going to a restaurant and ordering food and actually eating the food and stuff like that. I got this idea after I beat the game and I was walking around, it's really interesting, the city looks to be very alive but there's nothing to do afterwards. I would like those every day things to be in the game so you can feel that complete immersion. To feel that your character is actually alive would be an awesome thing. Maybe having the ability to make yourself a sandwich or actually cleaning your house, stuff like that. It already feels real and I'm just talking about making it a little bit more real and I'm not talking about the graphics either.

title: GTA 5 - Review
author: @Curly_Swivelman
comment: To really put in perspective. GTA IV came out in 2008. Following one of rockstar's greatest games of all time in 2010 came Red Dead Redemption literally one of the greatest games of our time. Upon that in 2011 Rockstar gave us LA Noire. A game that was a revolution at the time and even further in 2012 Max Payne a game that proved time doesn't matter in a video game's durability. Monumentally in 2013 Rockstar managed to pull off what was considered and is considered the greatest game of our generation Grand Theft Auto V only five short years after GTA IV they managed to accomplish all those games. I applaud you rockstar. Amazing to think that in 2 years time a new GTA may be hitting shelves.

title: GTA 5 - Review
author: @annamariegolden9220
comment:
I'll be honest I was a bit disappointed in this game... 

For one - the style of the missions seems to finally be showing its age. Second, the fact that you can't go inside buildings is almost maddening. In a weird way because of that one feature - it felt like a huge step back. The three character thing is cool - but i'm not sure there was ever a compelling enough reason to want to switch other than regular narrative reasons. 

The reviewer is right - it's def. the most polished GTA game yet; but it's an aged style of game that just didn't grab me in any way, shape or form like III, VC, SA, or IV did. Fun game - heck - great game. But it wasn't something that was blow away to me.

title: GTA 5 - Review
author: @michaelbiland5575
comment:
I'm very suspicious that Rockstar payed IGN to give Grand Theft Auto V a 10/10. I really enjoyed the game in general but it deserves a 9 or an 8.

Firstly, the combat and shooting is very downgraded and not at all as good as Rockstars previous entries such as Max Payne 3, Red Dead Redemption and even Grand Theft Auto IV.

Secondly, the physics and car damage are a complete joke compared to previous Grand Theft Auto games or ¬†other Rockstar titles. The car damage is not as realistic as even Grand Theft Auto III, and that's saying something.

Thirdly, the story and the characters are rubbish.

I'm not saying that the game is bad or terrible. But it has way more issues and problems than previous Grand Theft Auto or Rockstar titles.

title: GTA 5 - Review
author: @NEOSTHEATER
comment: So I'm hearing mixed thoughts about the story. It's my biggest problem with the game right now. I love sandbox games and definitely play a variety of genres of games but this games story is just....boring. Like I don't understand what it is that I'm missing. I enjoy Michael and Franklin's segments, (Trevor does make me laugh my ass off but can be pretty annoying and tiresome as well) and I do like the satiric take on today's modern culture but the missions all feel disjointed and like there is no over arching plot to the whole thing. I'd say I'm maybe like 35 to 40 percent through it and that's only because it feels like such a chore to try and get through. I can only play one mission before I get bored and have to put it down. I honestly only bought the game to have another game to play with my friend online but I'm that kind of person that must play the story before going online since sometimes there's control mechanics that you need to learn in the story first. I don't know, this is my first GTA game and I did get to play a little bit of GTA4 and Mafia 2 at another friends house and I honestly liked Mafia better but I just don't know how I feel about this game. I played through Watch Dogs and enjoyed that. I didn't love it but I also didn't go in super hyped up like everyone else did. I just thought it looked cool and it was cool. But it at least had a good flow to the story. You always knew what you were doing. Sleeping Dogs is kind of mix between Watch Dogs and GTA5 for me. I really didn't like Wei that much because the game didn't show him as a cop enough to make his sense of morality matter at all so he came off as kind of an ass but the gameplay was pretty good and again I usually always felt like the story had some direction that it was going in. So GTA5? Does it pick up later?

author: @trinekkini
comment:
Hilarious that GTA IV and V got 10s when GoW III got a 9.8. Bullshit IGN. Is Rockstar paying you to do this repeatedly?

GoW is considerably better than GTA in lighting, texture and visual graphics, and is comparable in scale, especially during epic boss battles. Sure GTA is a great game and I enjoyed playing it; but no way does it deserve a 10 when there ARE flaws (frame rate, minor bugs) and when comparable games don't get a 10 due to similar flaws.

The cars handle so much better but its not fun slamming them into a wall and only getting a little kink in the car. GTA IV was so much better at this which is why I loved playing just to demolish cars until I couldnt drive them anymore. GTA V is more arcade like this time but not for everyone. I loved GTA SA because of the countryside where you can drive like crazy through trails and fields. In GTA V Rockstar's sense of detail felt like they HAD to put a rock and hills in every square foot of the map so that was what killed it for me.

title: GTA 5 - Review
author: @barryaherne215
comment:
I'm with the minority who think this game didn't live up to expectation. The map is absolutely stunning, but I felt the story had little substance. The first 10 hours were superb, it ran out of steam quickly; the novelty wore off and I didn't care for the story after a while. I thought the heists got worse as the game progressed. Critiquing the game, I found myself praising GTA IV much more (pre-GTA V I had a decent - good opinion of it) as a lot of the good stuff in GTA V is from GTA IV; GTA V merely ¬†developed it more, refining it, but nothing as ground-breaking as the initial inceptions in IV. Personally though, I think some of my opinion stems from the fact that The Last Of Us was brilliant in terms of story-telling (and less so on scope) and Breaking Bad was ending (another story-driven franchise), and both came out weeks before GTA V, hence my criticism of the story in GTA. It was going to be difficult to top either in that department. But to each their own.

Overall, a very good game, probably a masterpiece in ambition and scope, but fails in terms of story in my opinion. Perhaps a 8.5 - 9.0 would have been a more accurate score for me.¬†

title: GTA 5 - Review
author: @knightlykin1499
comment: I really enjoyed how GTA V depicted security officers. I work security for a private company and they did well showing how the private sector work. In GTA V if you commit a crime in the view of a security guard you will get 1 star immediately and the guard will attack you. On my job, when we witness a crime we call police immediately and detain the criminal until the police arrive. Also in GTA when you punch a security guard he won't shoot you but instead pull a baton out and defend himself, in my job if someone attacks us hand to hand,¬†we would use pepper spray or a baton to bring the suspect down then detain him. And in GTA if you shoot at the¬†security officer¬†he will return fire with his pistol. In security we do carry firearms for our defense and the defense of other people and will return fire when we realize that lives are at stake. The game designer of GTA V did a perfect depiction of security officers as well as the private military contractors. Fantastic graphics, great activities etc. I do think it would be nice if they added boxing classes, and better clothing choices. I love GTA way more than Saints Row but I¬†like the idea of how Saints Row had the store "Make Pretend". If GTA adds a store like¬†that and lets you customize your character to look like a police officer, SWAT officer, security officer, soldier, bouncer, hazmat suit, flight suit¬†etc. This will make the game absolutely outstanding. And more vigilante work! No one wants to be just a cab driver, I liked shooting the bad guys in a police car, and putting out fires too! It would be sick if they added a vigilante job for the Merry weather patrol car, where it shows a property on the GPS, you drive to the property, patrol through it, and taser or fight the criminals committing crimes on the property. That would be a blast!

title: GTA 5 - Review
author: @BLARRRRRRRRRRGGGG
comment: Great game, but overall a major letdown. The story was great, but short and they didn't take full advantage of having 3 playable characters to have more individual missions (missions for each character). The ending seemed to be very rushed.  All of the arch enemies of the 3 main characters are killed in the same, boring way. GTA online is very fun, but filled with glitches. It seems Rockstar has fixed all of the glitches that are beneficial to the player and have forgotten about some other annoying glitches. The missions give almost no money and they are yet to add heist. This game had such high potential and it wasn't ultimately achieved. 8.6/10.

title: GTA 5 - Review
author: @armandopadilla-enea2057
comment:
The game's open world's asthetic COMPLETELY undermines the narrative! I haven't played the game yet. But I've seen just about every mission walkthrough on YouTube, and I was disappointed. GTA V felt like a dark comedy hard pressed on trying to be a Michael Bay film with its conjuction of gangsterism & overused explosive action; too many plots on trying to steal military weapons and vehicles from the government all while being on the continuous pursuit of the almighty dollar. On this note, the game doesn't take itself seriously.
Grand Theft Auto IV on the other hand was like watching a rich and vivid Martin Scorsese film. I really loved GTA IV because of its relatable character and its dark & gritty take on crime and the pursuit of the American Dream. Not to mention the fact that the reimagining of Liberty City unifies every single feature of the game.

To say that Rockstar shouldn't be merited for GTA V is wrong beyond fucking recognition, because they should! GTA V is an impressive looking game. I just feel that IV takes the cake here for the reasons stated.Ôªø

title: GTA 5 - Review
author: @ForeverRepublic
comment:
I honestly don't think this game deserves a 10. A 10 is for a once in a decade game that is a pure masterpiece, GTA V falls short of that mark. The ONLY enjoyable part of the story were the heist and the vast majority of the characters were forgettable. At times it is so cartoon-ish and crude to the point where I couldn't take it seriously. Los Santos is a generic city and the rest of the world isn't even worth visiting. There are pretty much no enjoyable side missions or random encounters and shootouts and police chases get boring very fast because the cops are terminators.¬†

I enjoyed the game, but it began to felt like a life simulator way to soon. If only they focused more, a lot more, on the story. It doesn't even come close to the God of all Rockstar Games: Red Dead Redemption. 7.8/10

title: GTA 5 - Review
author: @andrewstariha3362
comment: Great game, but it's very far from perfect. ¬†Definitely not worth a 10 in my opinion, but to be fair, our standards were pretty high. ¬†I was at least hoping they would fix the collectible system, which is still a massive pain in the ass with barely any rewards for completing. ¬†Not as bad as the pigeons in GTA 4, but still. ¬†The reticle is way too small, almost impossible to see at times, the hunting system is poorly implemented, tedious, and the money made is pathetic. ¬†Franklin is an absurdly underdeveloped character, and the game is a lot shorter than the others in the series. ¬†The world is huge, yes, but not very dense; there's massive areas with nothing to do in them whatsoever. ¬†The police obviously know exactly where you are during hiding sequences, and the game does a poor job of disguising this when they always zero in on your location without fail. ¬†Still great, but there's so many little flaws that the Rockstar diehard fans refuse to acknowledge.

title: GTA 5 - Review
author: @TheRealRobertBlarg
comment:
I have a question about this game. I think it looks bloody amazing and the only reasons I haven't gotten it yet are 1. because I have a few other games still to finish and I just KNOW this game will eat up my time and 2. I'm hesitant to get it when a next gen version might be just around the corner and I have a rule that I want to stick to: if a game is coming out for both current and next gen systems, I want the next gen version even if it's only slightly better because hey, it's slightly better.

Anyway, I've never really played the GTA series before... I love open world games and Rockstar makes some of the best if not THE best. I just couldn't get into GTA IV. Not exactly sure why. But Red Dead Redemption is a masterpiece IMO. Now, obviously... GTA and RDR are wildly different but one of my favorite things in RDR were the dynamic random world events: saving a girl from being raped, chasing down a store robber or a horse thief, being ambushed on the side of the road by outlaws who used an "innocent" woman to lure me over, all of that stuff. I love that kind of element to open world games. Spiderman 2 is another brilliant example.

It can get repetitive sure, but it's always nice to be able to load up a game and always have something to do even if the story is over. So... does GTA V have that sort of stuff? I know it definitely has side missions but RDR ALSO had side missions in the form of Stranger missions. So is there anything that just happens when you're driving around Los Santos and a little blip on the map appears, you go and investigate and.... something happens or no?

title: GTA 5 - Review
author: @xtensionxward3659
comment:
to point out some negative sides of this game that blinded hardcore fans miss :
1- 85% of this game is just driving around the city , including some key story parts evolve just in a speech mode while you're driving from point A to point B
2- missions get repetitive and you have to go through the same cycle of " preparing " to a heist¬† which is simply go across the city get an item then go across the city get the other item and when the mission starts the main action part is shooting a ridiculous amount of enemies , so yea same shit repeating itself
3-not much variety for example when franklin [ spoiler ] moved to another house i got¬† bored of it within 4 minutes because it offers nothing new¬† other than the swimming pool which you can't do anything in anyway , even calling relatives / friends will not give you anything but a conversation most of the time .
its nice to be able to run / drive around but in the middle of the game i just got bored and started only following main quests to get over with it , there is emptiness in the game which reminded me why i didn't like the previous ones , you can hate on me but i don't give a shit , this game is¬† 7 out of 10

title: GTA 5 - Review
author: @qg786
comment:
GTA V needed more missions... The heists in gta v where good but there wasn't enough classic gta missions. If you have your favourite food everyday you will get bored of it, just like doing nothing but heists on gta V got boring. Gta SA's Caligula's heist was good because there was other missions. Gta IV had good missions but the gameplay wasn't as good as V.

Also we need more Islands. There was no reason for me to explore the map on V. Having boundaries makes it a lot more anticipating. The previous gta's where good because I couldn't get to the next island, this made me wonder what rockstar has in store for me when I progress in the game. I didn't have that same feeling, not even 1%.

GTA IV online was a lot more fun than GTA V online, I don't want to worry about if I have enough money to buy cars, car mods, houses, weapons and ammunition. I just wan't to have fun. Not think about if I destroyed a personal vehicle or not. GTA IV's free mode was the most fun I've had. If they included a IV styled free mode as an option then I would play it more. Who didn't love battling it out at the airport on IV?

I hope the limitations GTA V had was because of the PS3 and Xbox 360 couldn't handle it, otherwise I'm starting to lose hope in this franchise.

title: GTA 5 - Review
author: @MisterMathematics
comment: Here are my two cents. Let me tell you right away - this game is outstanding. While the story was a little short, the missions were very fun. I bought GTA V on launch day and to this day the game disc is still in my PS3. I haven't taken it out from the system since September. There is a HUGE pile of stuff to do after the story (not counting multiplayer). And although there were some bugs in GTA Online, I wasn't really affected by them. GTA Online is so fun. The satisfaction that I got after buying myself my first expensive apartment in the game with my hard-earned money is something that I cannot describe. There is one thing that I disliked about this game. The atmosphere. I was so obsessed with Red Dead Redemption... it really felt like you were in the game. Here... not so much. Maybe it's because the game is set in 2013??? Who knows. 9.9/10

comment:
I cant believe this game had such high score. I dont know if reviewers are really hyped or are paid by publishers to give such a high score. Its true this game have a huge landscape and you can do a lot of things. That doesnt mean you can do a lot of things RIGHT, or that all the things you can do are fun. I have play for 10 hours now, an I cant believe the following:
1) The controls suck
2) Driving ir KIND OFF FUNNY
3) A lot of missions, drive from point A to point B kill and come back.
4) Why the hell is aiming so EASY and when you turn off the aiming aid it becomes impossible to kill anyone.
5) Why isnt there a good fighting mechanic?

This is not the first GTA, it is GTA 5. There is no excuse for those problems.

author: @ClubSoda98
comment: I wanted to like this game. I REALLY wanted to, but I just didn't. I quickly got bored of the game after playing for about 10 - 15 hours and I felt like playing it was a task. I was annoyed by EVERYONE spamming me with invites as well as the hate comments I got when I expressed my opinion to these people. I don't like how the game just is so plain dirty for the sake of being dirty. I'm not going to go over that as the reviewer covered it well. That's not to say I'm a prude, but take Borderlands 2 for example. I love that game as it has entertaining story, epic guns and loads of variety. It's just as crude, however I can't take it seriously due to the fact it's nothing like the real world. GTA V just seems like it's trying to hard to deviate and be controversial. I can appreciate all the effort that went into this game however and I can understand why people like it. I do still think that it should be given less.

title: GTA 5 - Review
author: @stevenwishart2600
comment:
Graphics are first class, game is first class. Best GTA made.

There is so much to do, fly planes, ride takes, steal takes and planes, ride bicycles, cars, drive 18 wheeler trucks, shoot mountain lions, shoot elk, shoot real estate signs, rip off famous movies stars memorabilia, you name it. The map is vast and so much to discover. You won't get bored at all. Just riding around in cars, trucks and planes makes this game worth it. You can fly 747 passenger planes. In one of the missions you fly a plane into the cargo hold of another, well thought out missions and super super fun.

I have seen some negative reviews and I can only explain them by the fact they have not played the game.

Only negative comment I can make, is there is too much swearing for my taste, but after all it is GTA.

Missions are great and enjoyable, having 3 characters is fun and doing missions as a trio is fun and well done.

Buy it, you won't regret it.

author: @danielwashington1
comment: Overall, GTA 5 is a good game. It's incredibly detailed and Rockstar was very innovative in terms of creating a game that has three protagonists. The only issues that I have with GTA 5 is the soundtrack and the way the storyline was structured. In terms of music, there were a few good songs here and there, but Rockstar could've done so much better with the game's music overall. As for the story, it would've been nice if Rockstar established a balance between playing all three protagonists during a few missions and playing only one protagonist during a few other missions. Those are just my personal opinions, but other than that, GTA 5 is an awesome game.

title: GTA 5 - Review
author: @aubreygreer
comment: This game really disappointed me. There was only 69 missions and they were divided between 3 characters, where as in GTA SA and IV, there were over 90 missions. Because the story was so short, I could never really get connected to the characters or their stories. It felt too much like an action movie with unrealistic, over-the-top missions over and over again. I get that the GTA IV's most popular mission was the heist mission, but don't make your whole game on one mission. It was the most popular mission because there was only one of them, which made it special. They really improved the gameplay, customization, and added more of a variety of stuff to do and access, which was missing in GTA IV. But what they didn't improve on was the writing and the story itself. GTA IV had the best story in a GTA game to date in my opinion, but GTA V's story felt rushed and not very well written. If you're going to have a game with 3 characters, then have 3 times the missions as well. I never really learned anything about the characters like I did in GTA 4 or Red Dead, which made me not care about them. Also the map is not as big as I hoped it would be, with many things unused like the prison and military base. I think a GTA game with a story like GTA 4 and gameplay like GTA V would be a perfect 10 game, but sadly, this game is overrated. Rockstar focused on story in GTA IV and not on gameplay, and in this game they focused on gameplay, and not much on story. When compared to games like GTA IV, Red Dead, Max Payne, and LA Noire, this game's story just doesn't compare. The idea is good, and it could've been better if the story was longer. I know I'm going to get hate from this, but that's just how I feel.

comment:
Honestly, this game is very good, but it does NOT deserve a 10.
The only really impressive thing about the game is its size. But most of the world is pretty rural and unpopulated so... meh.
Also, the characters, while funny, feel artificial and lack any sort of emotional depth. They just curse and shout cheesy one-liners the whole game.
The game is fun, but still buggy and unfair at times. The graphics are good for an open-world game but bland, but the load times blow.
This game is a 9.0 at best

title: GTA 5 - Review
author: @TheDieHard777
comment: Masterpiece, maybe not. But then again, what is meant by a masterpiece? If we consider a "masterpiece" to be something that has deep and meaningful themes, then GTA would be far from the mark. Yet its important to remember that we judge games based on their own merits, not by standards. I'll use the Last of Us. Great story, great gameplay. But mostly, I'll say it succeed in the story. You see, people don't judge that game by things like fun and action. They judge it by what it accomplished.

title: GTA 5 - Review
author: @phatcatrat
comment:
Because it'll take probably at least 6-8 years before nostalgia sets in. The time after a games release usually goes something like this: 
1. Uncontrolled Praising/Bashing of a game
2. People come to their senses and realize both the good and bad.
3. People get nostalgic, and don't remember the negative aspects of the game.
It's exactly what has happened with most major game releases.
